<font color="#FF0000">SURVIVING JUST &amp; UNJUST WARS</font><br>
<tt>Sat May 31  2:15:31 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
My father-in-law was a veteran of WWII and I am a veteran of the Vietnam war.  I noticed my father-in-law was hesitant to discuss his experiences.  Once I returned from Vietnam, he did relate several of his experiences flying C-47's from North Africa.  War was 'hell' for him also, even though he came home a 'hero'.  He has since died and I don't know whether he ever fully revealed all of his feelings about the war.<br><br>
Separate item:  I was a forward air controller in Vietnam and one thing I recall, that still frightens me, is that I experienced a sense of excitement each time I became involved in fight.  The fear is that I too, a mostly civil person, can become violent.
